<item>
            <title>[LU-7353] Segfault on lctl commands &apos;lctl network peer_list&apos; &apos;lctl network conn_list&apos;</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-7353</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;LFS performing normally. Admin issues lctl commands which result in segfaults.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&apos;lctl network peer_list&apos;&lt;br/&gt;
&apos;lctl network conn_list&apos; &lt;br/&gt;
each result in segfaults. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Attached core file resulting from &apos;lctl network peer_list&apos; executed on an OSS node.&lt;/p&gt;


</description>
                <environment>CentOS 6.6, 2.6.32-504.el6.x86_64, Lustre 2.7.56 / ZFS&lt;br/&gt;
(used Lustre 2.8 version as is closest to actual version)</environment>
