                            <comment id="131786" author="aeonjeffj" created="Wed, 28 Oct 2015 01:22:15 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Running &apos;lctl --net o2ib0 peer_list&apos; appears to function normally. Executing the lctl command with improper arguments results in either a segfault or no error at all.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&apos;lctl network peer_list&apos; results in a segfault&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&apos;lctl network o2ib0 peer_list&apos; results in no segfault, no stderr, exit 0&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&apos;lctl --net o2ib0 peer_list&apos; executes properly as expected.&lt;/p&gt;

</comment>
